> **CRITICAL — do not skip:** Day‑to‑day work = **host only**: UI **3055**, API **8000**, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000`. **Never** assume Docker `api` on 8000 is the code you are editing. Stop `api`/`frontend` containers if ports clash. See repo **`AGENTS.md`**.

## Canonical local setup (no Docker for app code)

This is how you always know what you are developing: **one UI port, one API port, both on the host.**

| Piece | Where to open / run |
|-------|---------------------|
| **UI** | **http://127.0.0.1:3055** — from `frontend/`: `npm run dev:3055` (or repo root: `npm run dev:frontend`) |
| **API** | **http://127.0.0.1:8000** (same as `http://localhost:8000`) — from repo root: `npm run dev:api` or `uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000` |

- In **root `.env`**, set **`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000`** (or `http://127.0.0.1:8000`) so the UI on **3055** calls the API you are editing.
- **Quick sanity check:** open **`http://localhost:8000/api/v1/docs`** (OpenAPI/Swagger). **`/docs`** alone may 404 — this app mounts docs under **`/api/v1/docs`**.

**Rule of thumb**

- **TouristGuideLocal in the browser = 3055** (not Docker’s published **3001** unless you intentionally use the container-built frontend).
- **The API you are editing = reload uvicorn on 8000** (or **8010** if 8000 is blocked on Windows).
- **Ignore 3001** for this app unless you deliberately want the Docker-built Next image.

## Why it felt messy

- **Docker** can expose **8000** (container API) and **3001** (container frontend). Your real local app for this repo is **3055**, not **3001**.
- Running **Docker `api` and local uvicorn both targeting 8000** means only one wins — you may think your code changed while still hitting the other process.

**Day-to-day dev without Docker:** stop the competing services, then run host UI + API:

```bash
docker compose stop api frontend
```

Postgres/Neo4j can stay up if your local API still uses the same DB URL (e.g. `localhost:5434`).

Compose note: **`docker compose up -d`** is wired so **Postgres + Neo4j** start by default; containerized **`api` / `frontend`** need **`docker compose --profile docker-api up`** (CI / parity). If you ever started the old container API: **`npm run docker:stop-api`** or `docker compose stop api frontend`.

## One command (optional)

From repo root: **`npm run dev`** — runs API + Next together (requires root **`npm install`** once for `concurrently`). Same ports: **8000** + **3055**.

## Fallback ports

| Issue | Use |
|-------|-----|
| **WinError 10013** on 8000 | `npm run dev:api:8010` and set **`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8010`**, restart Next |
| **3055 in use** | `npm run dev:frontend:3060` → open **http://127.0.0.1:3060** |

**Port audit:** `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/check-dev-ports.ps1`

## Agents

Prefer **`npm run dev`** or the canonical two-process setup above. Do not ask the user to rebuild Docker images to verify normal UI/API changes.
